{"section_number":"15.08","section_id":"91","structure_id":"16","catch_line":"Substitutes","history":"","full_text":"a Every effort shall be made to secure a substitute in the absence of an employee.\r\rb If it becomes necessary to have an employee substitute for an absent employee, the following selection procedure to determine which employee shall be required to do so shall be followed:\r\r1 Prior to the start of each school year, the employees in each building shall be sun\/eyed to determine which employees assigned to the building desire to volunteer for substitute teaching duty during the school year. Employees who indicate a desire to volunteer for such substitute teaching duty who are available to do so during the period required will be assigned the substitute teaching duty on a rotating basis.\r\r2 If no volunteer is available for the substitute teaching duty, the Principal shall have the right to require an available employee to perform the substitute teaching duty. If more than one employee is available during the period, assignments will be made on a rotating basis.\r\rc If an employee (other than an employee supervising a study period) is required by the Administration to substitute for an absent employee by taking the full or partial (at least one-half (1\/2) of the class) class of such absent employee, the employee will be paid Twenty Dollars ($20.00) per period for such work as an add-to pay.\r\rd An employee who is entitled to additional compensation pursuant to the provisions of this Section shall receive a verification of the substitute duty performed from the Building Principal by receiving a copy of the payment request form submitted to the Treasurers Office.\r\r","ancestry":{"1":{"id":"16","name":"Working Conditions","identifier":"XV","label":"Article","url":"http:\/\/localhost\/XV\/"}},"structure_contents":{"0":{"id":"84","structure_id":"16","section_number":"15.01","catch_line":"School Day","url":"http:\/\/localhost\/15.01\/","api_url":"http: